
Scope of the Project : BooksCart
	"Bookscart" aims to provide a seamless and user-friendly experience for book enthusiasts,
 connecting buyers and sellers in the world of literature. 
 The project's scope encompasses user management, product listings, 
 secure transactions, and support for both buyers and sellers, ultimately fostering a thriving online book marketplace.
 
 "Bookscart" is a web-based e-commerce platform designed to facilitate the buying and selling of books.
  Its scope includes the following key features and functionalities:
  
User Registration and Authentication: Users can create accounts, log in, and manage their profiles. Authentication ensures secure access to the platform.

Product Catalog: The platform maintains a catalog of books with details such as title, author, price, genre, and availability status. Users can search, browse, and filter books.

Shopping Cart: Users can add books to their shopping carts, review cart contents, and proceed to checkout for payment.

Order Processing: Book orders are processed securely, allowing users to provide shipping details and choose payment methods. Orders are confirmed with order IDs and status updates.

Payment Integration: Integration with payment gateways allows users to make secure online payments for their book purchases.

Order History: Users can view their order history and track the status of their book deliveries.

Responsive Design: Bookscart is designed to be accessible on various devices, including desktops, tablets, and mobile phones.

Content Management: Admins can manage website content, including banners, promotions, and announcements.
